<HEADLINE> Record Entry For World Athletic Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 14 (Xinhua) -- A record 209 countries will
participate in the World Athletics Championships in Athens in
August, an increase of 17 on the 1995 event, organizers said on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Organizing committee general manager Vangelis Savramis said the
biennial tournament would draw some 3,400 competitors, coaches and
officials.
</P>
<P>
The manager also said that all preparation works were going
"smoothly".
</P>
<P>
He added 52,000 tickets would go on sale this week with the
maximum price set at around 40 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
