<HEADLINE> 20 Kilograms of Gold Seized in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Twenty kilograms of gold worth
9.6 million rupees (about 274,000 U.S. dollars) were seized by
Indian customs officials in Mumbai (Bombay), Maharashtra, on
Sunday night from two brothers who arrived from the Gulf, Press
Trust of India reported today.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off, the officials recovered 85 gold bars each
from the checked-in baggage of the brothers who had walked through
the customs green channel.
</P>
<P>
The two brothers, whose nationalities were not disclosed, had
been detained.  
</P>
</TEXT>
