<HEADLINE> Chinese Women's Delegation Welcomed in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The friendship between Japan and
China must be enhanced and the peoples and governments of the two
countries should work together to ensure it, Ikuo Hirayama, the
Chairman of Japan-China Friendship Association, said today.
</P>
<P>
Hirayama was speaking at a welcome reception for a Chinese
women's delegation headed by Chen Muhua, the Chairwoman of the
All-China Women's Federation.
</P>
<P>
He said 1997 is the 25th anniversary of the normalization of
relations between Japan and China and further improvements should
be made in relations this year.
</P>
<P>
To enhance Sino-Japanese friendship, both sides should abide by
the Joint Statement of the Chinese and Japanese governments and
the Treaty of Peace and Friendship between the two countries, and
treat history properly.
</P>
<P>
Chen Muhua said that both China and Japan had benefitted a
great deal from the development of bilateral relations and she
hoped the two countries to make joint efforts for a better
future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
