<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Motorola Delivers 300 MHz Mac Compatible PC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Motorola Computer Group of the
U.S. today announced a Macintosh compatible new 300 MHz StarMax
computer that will hit the street in mid-May, at a time when the
market is losing test for Apple products.
</P>
<P>
Macintosh computers produced by Apple are becoming less visible
on the market. This new Motorala product will be the first Mac
OS-compatible system shipping with Mac Operating System 7.6 to
break the 300 MHz speed barrier.
</P>
<P>
The new personal computer is also to become one of the fastest
in speed if compared to other models offered by PC makers such as
IBM and Compaq.
</P>
<P>
Based on the PowerPC 603e chip, the StarMax 5000/300 minitower
system includes 512K L2 cache, Mac OS 7.6, 16x CD-ROM drive, 5 PCI
slots, 4.3 GB drive, 10BaseT Ethernet, 4 MB VRAM, 100 MB Iomega
Zip drive and software utility packages.
</P>
<P>
Motorola is also updating its existing StarMax product line
with newer versions of operating system and an adapter to enable
customers to use either PC or Mac monitors.
</P>
<P>
Apple's share of the U.S. retail personal computer market has
plunged to just 3 percent in February from 12 percent the year
earlier, according to the research firm Audits &AMP; Surveys
Worldwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
