<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Jobless Rate Remains at 10.8 Percent in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 14 (Xinhua) -- EU seasonally-adjusted
unemployment was 10.8 percent, the same as in the three previous
months, Eurostat, the European Union's statistical office,
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat said unemployment continued to fall in the United
Kingdom(7.1 percent), Ireland(11.6 percent) and the Netherlands(6
percent) but rised in Sweden(10.9 percent) and Portugal(7.3
percent). Elsewhere it seemed fairly stationary, it added.
</P>
<P>
Spain had by far the EU's highest rate of 21.7 percent,
Finland stood next at 15 percent. Lowest rate was Luxembourg's
3.4 percent, followed by 4.4 percent of Austria.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat estimated that 18.2 million people were unemployed in
the EU in February.  
</P>
</TEXT>
