<HEADLINE> Sysuyev Appointed Minister of Labor and Social </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
has appointed Oleg Sysuyev in the rank of Vice-Premier to head
the Ministry of Labor and Social Development by a Presidential
Decree, the Itar-Tass news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
At the same time by another Decree Gennady Melikyan has been
relieved of his duties of the Minister of Labour and Social
Development, the Itar-Tass quoted a source in the Presidential
press service as saying.
</P>
<P>
Sysuyev, 44, graduated from the Kuibyshev Aviation Institute
in 1976 and became Samara mayor in 1991. He was appointed to the
position of vice-prime minister by the presidential decree on
March 18, 1997.
</P>
<P>
As a vice-prime minister, Sysuyev is in charge of supervision
of social policy, reform of the social welfare system, the
preparation and implementation of laws in this area. He also
coordinates work in the areas of employment, migration, general
and vocational education and so on, as well as ensures interaction
between the government and trade unions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
