<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, April 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS -- France said Monday that it is encouraged by the
declarations made last weekend by Zairian President Mobutu Sese
Seko and Zairian rebel leader Laurent-Desire Kabila that they are
likely to hold direct talks.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel Monday announced that its Foreign Minister
David Levy would meet with Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat at
Tuesday's Euro-Mediterranean conference in Malta.
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- Zairean rebels have captured the town of Kananga,
capital of Western Kasai Province and one of the largest towns
outside Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
The town fell to the rebel forces on Saturday, a report
reaching here Monday morning said, quoting Voice of the People
Radio broadcast from the eastern town of Goma, where the rebel
headquarters is located.
</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- Greece's current accounts deficit reached 4.5 billion
U.S. dollars this year, compared to 2.8 billion dollars last year,
figures released by the bank of Greece said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The central bank attributed the increase mainly to the trade
deficit rise and invisible surplus drop.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia's gross domestic product (GDP) grew
year-on-year by 0.2 percent in the first quarter, a further sign
that the country's six-year slump may be over.
</P>
<P>
The small rise in GDP for the first quarter over the first
quarter of 1996, quoted by the State Statistics Committee, comes
three days after figures showing industrial output rose 0.7
percent over the same period.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Macedonia and the United States started a two-week
special joint military exercise codenamed "Commander 97" in
Macedonia, reports from Skoplje, capital of Macedonia said on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The first stage of the military exercise is in Skoplje and the
second will be in the Mavrova area of the landlocked Balkan
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
