<HEADLINE> Bomb Blasts in Addis Ababa's Biggest African </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- A bomb was exploded this
evening at Makato market, biggest African market in Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
According to witnesses, the bomb was exploded around 17:00
hours at the market and caused three dead and 17 injuries.
</P>
<P>
This is the second bomb explosions since last Saturday. There
were two blasts Saturday evening here. The blast which took place
at Tigrai hotel of the Piazza commercial center claimed the life
of a 25-year-old waitress and caused heavy and minor injuries to
33 others. The blast which occured at Bluetops, an Italian
restaurant caused injuries on eight foreigners, including four
Britains, two Frenchmen and two Jamaicans. 
