<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The abstention of opposition
UNITA leader Jonas Savimbi in the inauguration ceremony of the
new Angolan government can not constitute a crisis to the
country's peace process, U.N. envoy to Angola Blondin Beye said
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Savimbi, leader of the National Union for the Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA), failed to attend the inauguration
ceremony of the government of national unity and reconciliation
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, Beye was quoted by the Angolan News Agency today that
what's important is the government's assuming office, so the aim
has been reached.
</P>
