<DOCNO> XIE19970415.0037 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portuguese-Speaking States to Meet on Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- About 300 experts from seven
Portuguese-speaking countries will hold their third seminar on
water power and water resources here from Tuesday to Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Some 130 academic reports, 30 from Mozambique, 60 from
Portugal and 40 from Brazil, will be read during the seminar,
also called SILUSBA III, Rui Gonzales, a spokesman for the
seminar, said here today.
</P>
<P>
Among the main topics are water resources management,
irrigation and drainage, environment and water power, he said.
</P>
<P>
Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano and Foreign and
Cooperation Minister Leonardo Simao will attend the seminar's
opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The first seminar of this kind was held in Portugal's capital
Lisbon in 1994 and the second in Recife, Brazil in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
