<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Zairian rebels led by
Laurent-Desire Kabila confirmed today that they captured last
Friday the city of Kasumbalesa, south of Lubumbashi and on the
Zairian-Zambian border.
</P>
<P>
The Goma-based rebel radio, "Voice of People," said, "The
liberation army, the unconquerable machine, swept the cities and
areas to eject the enemies of the people. Kasumbalesa fell without
resistance."
</P>
<P>
The rebels also said that the capital of the Western Kasai
region, Kananga, "was quickly abandoned by the FAZ (the Zairian
government army)" last Friday.
</P>
<P>
"It was there where (President) Mobutu made his first step in
the army," said the radio report.
</P>
<P>
Over the past seven months, the Zairian rebels conquered nearly
half of the country's territory, including its richest areas.
</P>
<P>
"It (the rebel force) will go up till the sea to prove to the
world its determination," said the radio.
</P>
<P>
Kabila has claimed that his force can capture the capital
Kinshasa "well before June."  
