<HEADLINE> Father Jailed for Domestic Hooliganism on Daughter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 14 (Xinhua) -- A 48-year-old father was given 18
months in jail and three years under police guidance by a Paris
court today for domestic hooliganism on his 28-year-old daughter,
reported the Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
Jacques Girard, a self-styled writer and scenerist, tried twice
to strangle his daughter, Isabelle, after watching a football
match on television in their home in Trappes outside Paris on
March 4.
</P>
<P>
Girard, who had been separated from his wife for several years,
was unemployed, did not have a fixed home, and was only allowed by
his wife to go to their home for supper each evening.
</P>
<P>
He assaulted Isabelle after watching television, under the
cheerings of his 20-year-old son, Patrick, who shouted:"Kill her!
Kill her!"
</P>
<P>
The girl managed to get away from his paws and called police,
who subdued him and took him away.
</P>
<P>
The court also banned Girard from re-visiting the area where
his family live after he is out of prison, and ordered a doctor to
provide medical and psychological care to Isabelle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
