<HEADLINE> Dozens of Students Arrested in Front of German </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Dozens of Iranian students were
arrested by anti-riot policemen as they tried to break through a
protective line in a bid to seize the German flag at the top of
German Embassy here today.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses told Xinhua that there were clashes between some
400 university students and 1,000 policemen who beat and kicked
the demonstrators away from the compound of the German Embassy.
</P>
<P>
However, a well-informed source said that most of the
students who were arrested by the police have been released
under the pressure of other students.
</P>
<P>
The students staged a 90-minute demonstration in front of the
German Embassy while trying to enter the compound to express what
they called Iran's fury over its leadership being implicated by
the Berlin court in an alleged political assassination.
</P>
<P>
Chanting "Death to Germany" and "Death to the Zionist judge,"
the students warned that they would seize the German Embassy
unless the German government make a formal apology to the Iranian
nation and retreat from hostility against Iran.
</P>
<P>
Some of them tried to negotiate with the police about the
entry into the German Embassy compound and some tried to break
through the six human protective chains formed by the policemen,
shouting "We will occupy the embassy and pay back the insult
against our sanctities and leaders."
</P>
<P>
Eventually the students began dispersing while the police
maintained their huge presence in the downtown area in a bid to
prevent further attempt to break into the German Embassy by the
students, a likely prospect reminiscent of what happened to the
U.S. embassy 18 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration was organized by the University Islamic
Society.
</P>
<P>
The move is the harshest reaction from the Iranian students
in the past four days since the ruling of the Berlin court
which charged Iran's top political leaders with ordering the
assassination of four Kurdish opposition leaders in a restaurant
five years ago.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that police had
cordoned off the whole Ferdowsi street leading to the embassy. The
demonstration caused traffic jam in the streets nearby the
embassy where the police prevented the protesters from reaching
the embassy.
</P>
<P>
This was the third demonstration held by Iranians within a
week in the wake of the ruling of the Berlin court
regarding the Mykonos case verdict.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Iran launched a nationwide anti-German wave with
tens of thousands of people turning out to streets to protest
against the Berlin court verdict.
</P>
<P>
Similar demonstrations were also held in 12 Iranian cities,
including Qom, Shiraz and Tabriz.
</P>
<P>
Demonstrators urged the Iranian government to sever diplomatic
relations and economic ties with Bonn and to prosecute German
firms which provide chemical weapons to Iraq during the war with
Iran between 1980 and 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
