<HEADLINE> Kenya, Rwanda, Uganda to Hold Summit on Burundi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Presidents of Kenya,
Rwanda and Uganda have respectively confirmed their participation
in the fourth Great Lakes Region summit on Burundi in Arusha,
northern Tanzania on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Director of Information, Policy and Research in the Ministry
of Foreign Affairs Cyprian Majengo said today the presidents of
Zaire, Burundi, Zambia, Ethiopia and Cameroon have been invited
to the summit summoned by Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa.
</P>
<P>
"We hope all invited presidents will attend the summit. We are
optimistic that those who are yet to confirm will do so between now
and April 16", said Majengo.
</P>
<P>
However, the summit will be attended by the chief mediator on
Burundi, retired Tanzanian President Mwalimu Julius Nyerere, he said.
</P>
<P>
The summit would evaluate political situation in Burundi and
economic sanctions imposed on the country and the way forward,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Majengo said senior officials involved met today to deliberate
on the latest security developments in the central African
country to be proceeded by the ministerial technical committee
meeting Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Secretary General of the Organization of
African Unity (OAU), Salim Ahmed Salim, was also expected to
attend the summit.
</P>
<P>
Local reports said Nyerere was to submit his report at the
summit on the progress made so far in ending the crisis and it
would be the basis of talks among the leaders of the Great Lakes
Region on whether to lift or tighten the sanctions imposed on
Burundi by Tanzania, Kenya, Uganda, Rwanda and Zaire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
