<HEADLINE> Cameroun and Malaysia Seek Further Economic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Cameroun and Malaysia are palm
oil producing countries and should seize the opportunity to share
their experiences, said Ndioro Justin, the Camerounian minister
of trade and industry in Yaounde this morning while meeting with
the visiting Malaysian business delegation.
</P>
<P>
Headed by Lim Keng Kaik, the Malaysian minister of primary
industry, the 42-men Malaysian business delegation is in Cameroun
to contact with Camerounian business partners on investment
possibilities.
</P>
<P>
Lim Kaik said the purpose of the dialogue is to provide a
forum to discuss the investment opportunity in the timber and
palm oil industries and also to share Malaysia's experiences in
developing the timber and palm oil industries, he added that
Malaysian scientists and experts are willing to help Camerounians
acquire technique know-how and proper planatation management in
oil palm development.
</P>
<P>
According to Lim Kaik, agriculture sector, in particular the
primary commodity sector, plays an important role in the
development of the country. The basis of Malaysia's strong timber
industry lies in the sound management of the forestry resources.
Exports receipts from timber and timber products amounted for 5.5
billion U.S. dollars in 1996. As for oil palm, Malaysia has
established itself as the largest producer and exporter of palm
oil accounting for 53 percent and 63 percent of the world total
production in 1996.
</P>
<P>
While in Cameroun, the agriculture and forestry sector is an
important component of the country's economy, providing
employment for majority of the population.
</P>
<P>
The businessmen from the two countries are now exploring the
possibility of setting up joint-ventures in timber and palm oil
industries.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia initiated its economic practises in the central
African countries since last year. Some Malaysia companies
invested in the countries like Cameroun, Equatorial Guinea. They
mainly work on forest exploration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
