<HEADLINE> Daredevil Buys Insurance for Driving Across Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 15 (Xinhua) -- A daredevil bought an insurance
here today for his driving across the Yellow River on June First
this year.
</P>
<P>
The Xi'an branch of the People's Insurance Company of China was
the first in the country that is willing to take the risk for some
60 million yuan of insurance for the activity, including one
million yuan of life insurance for Ke Shouliang.
</P>
<P>
Ke, who rode a motorcycle across the Great Wall in 1992, plans
to drive a car across the 50-m-wide Hukou Waterfall of the Yellow
River which is the border of north China's Shanxi Province and
northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Ke is expected to drive from the Shanxi side to the Shaanxi
side. He has only 200 meters of run-up land.
</P>
<P>
As part of his preparing efforts, Ke succeeded in driving
across an area of 43 m wide recently in south China's Guangdong
Province.  
</P>
