<HEADLINE> Mauritius Trade Delegation to Visit Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 15 (Xinhua) -- A high-level Mauritius trade
delegation led by its prime minister will arrive in Hong Kong on
Thursday on a mission to promote bilateral trade, it was announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the mission is to boost total trade between
Mauritius and Hong Kong to 1.2 billion HK dollars (150 million
U.S. dollars), up from 1.01 billion HK dollars (129 million U.S.
dollars) in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The 45-member delegation led by Prime Minister Navinchandra
Ramgoolam and Financial Minister Vasant Bunwaree also comprises
officials from the Mauritius Offshore Business Activities
Authority (MOBAA), Mauritius Freeport Authority (MFA) and 38
private corporations.
</P>
<P>
Of Mauritius' total trade of 1.01 billion HK dollars with Hong
Kong last year, 930 million HK dollars (119.2 million U.S.
dollars) were exports from Hong Kong to Mauritius and over half of
them were textiles.
</P>
<P>
The mission will present the offshore business activities and
freeport facilities available in the country at a seminar next
Monday. The delegation will also hold individual meetings with
Hong Kong business people. 
</P>
