<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has revamped its
tourism organizations to more effectively make money from visitors
to the metropolis.
</P>
<P>
The Municipal government announced here today that two agencies
were formed to outline comprehensive plans and coordinate the
city's tourism development.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Tourism Management Committee (TMC) and Shanghai
Tourism Working Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
replaced a group in charge of Shanghai's tourism and the bureau of
Shanghai tourism management.
</P>
<P>
The newly organized Shanghai TMC will manage the whole
municipality's tourism as a functional agency of the municipal
government.
</P>
<P>
Gong Xueping, vice-mayor and director of the TMC, said that
Shanghai will make tourism a new pillar industry of the city as
early as possible.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's tourism will be strongly colored with the style of
metropolis.
</P>
<P>
Gong said that only 216,000 people are involved in tourism,
making 4.6 percent of all employees of the city. The tourism
development will provide more job opportunities for those
laid-offs and unemployed people.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai promises a great market for tourism, too, said
Gong. He said that the city is building a transportation network
that will be quick and convenient.
</P>
<P>
There are over 260 travel agents, 118 star-level hotels with
over 30,000 rooms in Shanghai. 
