<HEADLINE> Liu Huaqing Meets with Russian Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Chairman of China's Central
Military Commission Liu Huaqing said here today the establishment
and advancement of the Sino-Russian strategic cooperative
partnership catering to the needs of the 21st century is not only
in the fundamental interests of the Chinese and Russian peoples,
but conducive to the regional and global peace, stability, and
development.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with the visiting Russian Minister of National
Defense Igor Nikolayevich Rodionov, Liu said China and Russia, and
their armed forces enjoy a good relationship, and the growth of
this relationship has a solid foundation.
</P>
<P>
Liu, who is also a Standing Committee member of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, described
Rodionov's trip to China as an important one.
</P>
<P>
He briefed the Russian visitors on China's economic situation
and its armed forces as well.
</P>
<P>
"We develop our own country to bring happiness to the Chinese
people. This is also conducive to the world peace and stability."
Liu stressed, "No matter what great development our nation will
achieve, we will not pose threat to other countries, but will make
still greater contributions to world peace and stability."
</P>
<P>
The "China threat theory" spread by a small number of people
in some countries is totally "groundless," he said.
</P>
<P>
Rodionov said China and Russia are great neighbors. The
establishment and develoment of the strategic cooperative
partnership between the two countries are entirely in the interests
of the two countries and their peoples, and are conducive to the
peace and stability of the Asia-Pacific region and the world.
</P>
<P>
Rodionov, who is on his first visit to China as minister of
national defense, pointed out his trip is intended to enhance the
development of the friendship and cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Russian army is willing to step up the exchange and
cooperation with the Chinese army, he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Fu Quanyou, chief of the general staff of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army, and Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of the general
staff, attended the meeting.  
</P>
