<HEADLINE> Italian Senate Votes to Lift Embargo Against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The Italian Senate today called on
the government to support the gradual lifting of the United
Nations seven-year embargo against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The upper house of parliament passed a resolution calling on
the Italian government to take the initiative in international
forums for the progressive lifting of the embargo imposed on Iraq
after its invasion of Kuwait in 1990, and releasing Iraqi assets
frozen in the banks of member countries of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The senate also passed a resolution appealing to the government
to support the humanitarian campaign of non-governmental
organizations to guarantee the fundamental rights of Iraqi
citizens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
