<HEADLINE> Liatti Leads in Spain Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Italian Piero Liatti took the lead
in the Spain Rally on Tuesday after the 10th stage.
</P>
<P>
The Subaru driver edged his British team-mate Colin McRae and
Finnish reigning world champion Tommi Makinen to finish the 10th
stage at La Figuera, repors reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Liatti, who was two seconds ahead of McRae, begun the second
day just one second behind McRae, the overnight leader.
</P>
<P>
Makinen, who started the day 12 seconds off the lead, closed in
during the day's first four stages to lie just one second adrift
of McRae.
</P>
<P>
Spaniard Carlos Sainz, who suffered a puncture earlier in the
day, lost five minutes on the 10th stage with a broken propshaft
which completely crashed his podium-finish hope.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's remaining three stages will take the teams back to
Lloret de Mar for an overnight stop before the final leg begins
early on Wednesday morning. 
</P>
