<HEADLINE> China to Strictly Implement State's Environment Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- China today asked governments at
all levels to strictly implement the State's decision on
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The State Bureau of Environmental Protection (SBEP) and the
Ministry of Supervision at a news briefing here today that they
will examine the governments' implementation of the decision
issued last year by the State Council on environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Xie Zhenhua, the SBEP's director said that the decision is a
programmatic document of the country's environmental protection
work and the basic guarantee for the country to fulfill its
environment blueprint by 2010.
</P>
<P>
Since the issue of the decision, the country has scored
remarkable progress in environmental protection, Xie said,
however, some government officials are still not determined,
especially when the regional interests are infringed upon.
</P>
<P>
Xie said that the State Council has asked the SBEP to check the
regional governments' efforts at fighting pollution with the help
of the supervision departments.
</P>
<P>
The inspection this time is to give a push to the pollution
control throughout the country, Xie noted, adding that the
officials who act against the decision are "sure to receive severe
punishment."
</P>
<P>
Xie stressed that they will mainly check the governments'
efforts this time, and formalism should be "resolutely" opposed.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Xiaodong, an official with the Ministry of Supervision
said that his ministry will pay close attention to the
examination, and will co-operate with the SBEP to improve the
environmental awareness of governments at all levels.
</P>
<P>
"Violation of disciplines and corruption in the pollution
control move will be dealt with seriously," Zeng said.
</P>
<P>
Six inspection groups will soon head for 17 provinces,
municipalities, and autonomous regions including Chongqing,
Zhejiang, Guangdong, and Xinjiang. The inspection is expected to
last two months.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
