<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Seeks Cooperation with Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is ready to step up
cooperation with Sri Lanka in city construction, Beijing Mayor Jia
Qinglin said today in a meeting with visitors from Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Jia told this to visiting Nimal Siripala De Silva, minister of
Housing, Construction and Public Utilities of Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
He welcomed Sri Lanka's involvement in Beijing's city
construction. He proposed that the two sides can discuss
specific cooperation projects.
</P>
<P>
Silva expressed gratitude to towards China for providing
assistance to Sri Lanka in economic and construction areas, saying
that Beijing enjoys a very good reputation for the quality of
projects it undertakes in Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
A Beijing construction company has won a bidding to
build several waterworks in Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Silva invited Beijing construction companies to contract for
other projects in Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Silva, who visited China 13 years ago, spoke highly of
Beijing's tremendous changes in city construction. He hoped that
his current visit would promote cooperation between Beijing and
Sri Lanka in this regard.  
</P>
</TEXT>
