<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Ferrets out Drug Sellers and Abusers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Police in South China's
Guangdong Province have ferreted out 361 people selling or using
head-rocking pills, a new kind of drug, in Guangzhou and
Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Head-rocking pills, making abusers shake their heads as though
dancing rock-and-roll for hours, have been identified by doctors
as causing fatal damage to the abusers' organs.
</P>
<P>
Having been popular among western drug abusers for years, the
pills were first found in China in October last year in dancing
halls in such large cities as Shanghai and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Recently, police in Guangzhou and Shenzhen ferreted out 361
people selling or using the drugs and confiscated nearly 1,000
head-rocking pills.
</P>
<P>
Local police officials say that the pill sellers will be
seriously punished, and the abusers will also be punished.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
