<DOCNO> XIE19970415.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-15 13:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hamas Calls for Escalation of anti-Israeli </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The militant Islamic
Resistance Movement (Hamas) today called on Palestinians to
intensify their violent struggle against Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
In a leaflet received by Xinhua, Hamas denounced Israel for
having imposed a total military closure on the Palestinian
village Kafr Ysurif near Hebron since the March 21 suicide
bombing in Tel Aviv, in which four people including the Hamas
suicide bomber Moussa Ranimat were killed.
</P>
<P>
Ranimat was living in Kafr Ysurif. His home has been recently
destroyed by Israel as a form of punishment, leaving his wife and
four children homeless.
</P>
<P>
The militant group charged the closure had caused the death of
four Palestinian patients at Israeli checkpoints after they were
refused entry to receive medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
"What is happening in Ysurif reflects the Israeli policy of
collective punishment against our unarmed citizens," the leaflet
said.
</P>
<P>
"We declare our solidarity with our Palestinian brothers and
sisters in Ysurif who are confronting the Zionist terror. We
call upon all Palestinians to escalate their blessed Intifada
(Arab uprising) all over Palestinian lands," it noted.
</P>
<P>
Hamas also slammed the Palestinian National Authority (PNA)
for helping Israeli security services to crack down its
activists.
</P>
<P>
Since Israel decided in March to build the Har Homa Jewish
settlement in controversial East Jerusalem, Palestinian
protesters across the Palestinian territories have been clashing
with Israeli soldiers by throwing stones and petrol bombs. So far
three Palestinians have been killed and hundreds of others
wounded in the current wave of violence.
</P>
<P>
Following the March Tel Aviv bombing, Israel has imposed a
total closure on the Palestinian territories, barring tens of
thousands of Palestinian workers from entering Israel to
work. The closure was only eased in the past days after the
situation became relatively calm.
</P>
<P>
But a new flare-up of violence can be triggered because of
the deadlocked Israeli-Palestinian peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Israel has conditioned the resumption of peace talks with the
Palestinian side on the PNA's commitment to launching a long-term
crackdown on Hamas and other Palestinian militant groups.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
