<HEADLINE> Italian Troops Set Off for Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Italian Defense Minister Beniamino
Andreatta today gave a formal send-off in Bridisi to Italian
troops bound for Albania to protect the humanitarian relief
operation and help stabilize the Balkan country.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta, accompanied by Chief of Staff Admiral Guido
Ventoroni, arrived in Bridisi today and reviewed the troops, the
Defense Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
