authorizing the dispatch of a 6,000-strong Italian-led
multinational force for three months to protect relief
operation in the crisis-hit nation.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 people have been killed in two months of unrest
in Albania sparked by the collapse of popular pyramid savings
schemes last December.
</P>
<P>
Much of southern Albania is still under control of armed
protesters who insist that President Sali Berisha resign over the
fraudulent schemes in which thousands of Albanian families lost
their savings. 
