<HEADLINE> Export Commodities Fair Opens in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The Eighth China Fair of Export
Commodities from Foreign-Funded Enterprises opened today in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Exhibitors included more than 250 foreign-funded enterprises
from 21 provinces, municipalities, and autonomous regions, such as
Jiangsu and Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Their exhibited commodities fall into the categories of light
industry, arts and crafts, textiles, clothing, machinery, and
electronics.
</P>
<P>
To date, China has approved more than 270,000 overseas-funded
enterprises since it initiated the reform and open-up policy in
1979, more than 130,000 of which have gone into operation,
employing more than 14 million people, sources say.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the country's exports reached more than
150 billion US dollars last year, with 41 percent from
overseas-funded enterprises.  
