<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Chairman of the Standing
Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC) Wang Hanbin
met with a delegation from the National Assembly of the Congo led
by its president Andre Milongo here today.
</P>
<P>
Wang met with the Congo delegation on behalf of the Chairman of
the NPC Standing Committee Qiao Shi.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Wang said the two countries share a
traditional friendship, and that the Congo is among the earliest
African countries that forged diplomatic ties with China. Despite
the changes in the world situation and the internal situation of
Congo, he added, the two countries have always supported and
helped each other in the past few decades.
</P>
<P>
The friendship between the two countries has withstood the test
of time and serves as an example of South-South cooperation, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Links between the NPC and the parliament of Congo have also
become closer, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Milongo said that the two countries have much common interest
and never had any conflict. He stressed that the Congo has always
adhered to the "one China" policy and will continue to support
China's course of peaceful reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
He expressed appreciations on China's assistance to his country
in the fields of economy, culture, science and technology, public
health, and education. He hopes that the two countries will expand
cooperation into wider areas, such as high technology.  
