<HEADLINE> Mandela Invites Gullit To Play Friendly Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Dutch international star Ruud
Gullit has been asked by Nelson Mandela to play a soccer friendly
match in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The South African leader asked Gullit to join the Dutch
national squad for a special match against South Africa in
Johannesburg on June 1.
</P>
<P>
The friendly international is billed as the Nelson Mandela
Inauguration Challenge, an annual event since 1994.
</P>
<P>
Gullit, former Feyenoord and AC Milan player, was named
European Footballer of the year in 1987 and he dedicated his honor
to Mandela, at the time still in prison.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch, now player-coach of the Chelsea club, has said an
invitation from Mandela would be a great honor and one he would be
pleased to accept.
</P>
<P>
Gullit, who is recovering from the ankle injury, was ruled out
of the rest of Chelsea's matches this season.
</P>
<P>
He has not played for the Dutch national team since he quitted
before the 1994 World Cup due to a tactical disagreement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
