<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seven Chinese Businessmen Sentenced to Prison for Piracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Seven Chinese businessmen were
sentenced to prison for pirating video and audio compact disks,
the Supreme People's Court announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Bu Xinghua, former deputy general manager of the Suzhou Baodie
Compact Disk in the east China province of Jiangsu, was sentenced
to 17 years' jail term for pirating 3.13 million audio and video
compact disks and had illicit sales of 12.06 million yuan, the
court said.
</P>
<P>
Bu committed the piracy in collaboration with Zhong Jiansheng,
deputy manager of the company's business department during the
period between September 1994 and November 1995 when he and Bu
were in charge of the company, according to the court.
</P>
<P>
The company was also convicted of pirating and manufacturing
130,000 pornographic VCDs, from which it made an illicit profit of
690,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Zhong Jiansheng was sentenced to 11 years' imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
The court also asked the company to pay a penalty of 200,000
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Bu was also found to have taken bribes of 15,000 yuan and 4,900
Hong Kong dollars, taking advantage of his position and power, the
court said.
</P>
<P>
In another court verdict, Wang Binyan, former chairman and
general manager of the Caixiang Audio and Video Products
Manufacturing Ltd and its parent company, the Guangdong Audio and
Video Publishing House, was sentenced to four years' imprisonment
for processing and manufacturing 5.08 million pirated CDs and VCDs
for the outlaws, the court said.
</P>
<P>
The company was paid 26.42 million dollars and 1.43 million
Hong Kong dollars for illegally processing the pirated CDs and
VCDs.
</P>
<P>
The company's four other employees who were involved in the
piracy, including deputy general managers Zhang Yongxiang, Liang
Zhaopeng, manager of the production department, Li Yanxia, and
manager of the financial department Liu Yongjin were given
sentences from three years to one and half years respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
