<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Firmer After Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
clawed back most of Monday's losses to close firmer today as
stocks across the board benefited from a rebound on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark All Ordinaries Index closed 15.6 points stronger
at 2381.7.
</P>
<P>
"The local market performed well although local investors
remained concerned about the U.S. market's next direction with
inflation figures out tonight," Nevitts broker Steve Mayne said.
</P>
<P>
The All Industrials Index absorbed most of today's gains,
rising 28.1 points to 3745.4 while the All Resources Index went up
5.3 points to 1330.2.
</P>
<P>
Energy stocks were a highlight, helped by firmer oil prices
overnight and positive outlooks for drilling programs.
</P>
<P>
Gold stocks made tentative gains with the gold index closing
7.2 points firmer at 1558.8.
</P>
<P>
In the banking sector, Commonwealth Bank gained 18.3 cents and
Westpac 5 cents while ANZ was steady and National Australia Bank
edged 0.7 cents higher.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 250.77 million shares valued at
674.78 million Australian dollars (526.32 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
