<HEADLINE> Port of Entry in Jilin Opens Wider to Outside World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The Quanhe Port of Entry, which
has in the past only been open to Chinese and residents of
Democratic People's Republic of Korea, became passable for foreign
travelers earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
The outlet in Huichun City, Jilin Province, is the only passage
leading to a free trade zone of the Democratic People's Republic
of Korea (DPRK). The recent move is seen as a start for upgrading
the outlet into a Category One Port of Entry.
</P>
<P>
From this month on, foreign travelers holding a valid passport
and visa can go out of China through the port of entry.
</P>
<P>
Those who have entered the DPRK and want to return to China
should arrange a visa in advance in China, local officials said.
</P>
</TEXT>
