<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Further Strengthen Ties With Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Foreign Minister Abdus
Samad Azad today held talks with the visiting Foreign and Law
Minister of Singapore S. Jayakumar on bilateral and other issues
of common concern, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers had an overview of the state of ties,
expressed satisfaction over the growing links and explored
possibilities of expanding cooperation in different fields between
their countries.
</P>
<P>
The two sides discussed trade relationship and agreed to
increase the economic and trade links. The total turnover of
bilateral trade is about 1 billion U.S. dollars and Bangladesh
exports account for only 40 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi side in the talks stressed the need for
Singapore to increase exports from the country, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Dhaka also wants more Singapore investment, which is
relatively low compared with the capital Singapore has put in
Bangladesh's neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh's membership in the Indian Ocean Rim (IOR) was also
discussed and Singapore, which is an active member of the group,
has reportedly assured of its support on this matter.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Sunday, the Singapore foreign minister called on
Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, who said her country
could benefit from the experience of Singapore in urban
development and managing airports and seaports.  
</P>
