<HEADLINE> China's Move to Develop High-Performance Computers Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- A series of Chinese-made
high-performance computers have been used in a major information
project of Tianjin, breaking up foreign corporations' monopoly
over this slice of the market.
</P>
<P>
Qu Weizhi, vice-mayor of Tianjin, made the announcement at
today's press conference on the successful application of
high-performance computers made by the Dawning Information
Industry Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Dawning is a high-tech company created as a result of the
achievements of China's hi-tech program, and is a leading maker of
high-performance computers in China.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin first began experimenting with the use of advanced
computers in November, 1996. It plans to invest 140 million yuan
(about 17 million US dollars) in launching an information project,
using 200 Dawning series products.
</P>
<P>
As many as 50 Dawning computers have been used in the project,
covering tax collection management, scientific research, commerce
and trade, and foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Dawning Corp., established in Shenzhen in 1995, is a key
vehicle for technology transfer and commercializing the research
findings of the national high-tech program. 
</P>
