<HEADLINE> Arafat Arrives in Malta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VALLETTA, MALTA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National
Authority President Yasser Arafat arrived here today to attend
the second European-Mediterranean conference.
</P>
<P>
He will be attending the conference with Israeli Foreign
Minister David Levy and ministers from 25 other European and
Mediterranean countries.
</P>
<P>
The conference, to focus on how to push forward the Euro-Med
cooperation launched at the first Barcelona conference in 1995,
is also expected to discuss the faltering of the Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli-Palestinian talks have been virtually brought to
a halt as the Israeli hardline policies, particularly the Jewish
settlement plans in East Jerusalem, angered the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League decided on March 31 to stop normalization
process of their relations with Israel, revive the economic
boycott and withdraw from Mideast multilateral talks.
</P>
<P>
Reports say that Arafat might meet Levy bilaterally during the
conference on ways to defuse the current crisis and get the peace
talks back on track.
</P>
<P>
European officials have said here that European Union's (EU)
Middle East Envoy Miguel Angel Moratinos has been trying to
broker an Arafat-Levy meeting in Malta.
</P>
<P>
The two-day conference is to open later today and bring
together ministers from the 15 EU members and their 12
Mediterranean partners, namely Algeria, Cyprus, Egypt, Israel,
Jordan, Lebanon, Malta, Morocco, Syria, Tunisia, Turkey and
Palestine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
