Straits Times Industrials Index fell by merely 1.67 points to
close at 2032.97 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 149.23 million units, worth
364.45 million Singapore dollars (about 253.09 million U.S.
dollars). Declines again overwhelmed advances 251 to 86, while 272
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Westmont Land was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 12.85 million units. It was followed by
Kuala Lumpur Ind. which had 8.21 million shares traded. The
Neptune Orient Lines, the Singapore government-linked shipping
firm, was next with 7.27 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led the gainers of the day as it rose by 1 dollar
to finish at 17.7 Singapore dollars. The Singapore Press Holdings
(SPH) gained 30 cents to end at 12.4 Singapore dollars, while
local car distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) picked up 20 cents to
close at 15 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Malaya Banking was the biggest loser of the
day as it declined by 1.2 Singapore dollars to end at 15 dollars.
First Capital fell by 50 cents to close at 3.3 Singapore dollars,
while Sungei Way finished 40 cents lower at 3.6 Singapore dollars.
</P>
