<HEADLINE> W. Africa's Financial Institute Starts Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The newly-launched West African
Institute for Financial and Economic Management (WAIFEM) is to
start its inaugural training program in Nigeria's largest trade
center of Lagos on Wednesday, said its press release today.
</P>
<P>
WAIFEM was jointly established here last week by central bank
governors of the five west African English-speaking countries,
namely, Nigeria, Ghana, Liberia, the Gambia and Sierra Leone,
together with the International Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
The institute, based in the Satellite Town, Lagos, will focus
its programs on middle-and-senior-level employees of the central
banks, ministries of finance and economic planning.
