<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Rong Yiren
met here this morning with Former Philippine Vice-President
Salvador H. Laurel at the Great Hall of the People, where the two
leaders disussed the broad scope of friendly cooperative ties that
exist between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Laurel who has visited China three
times, Rong cited Laurel as an old friend of the Chinese people
who has contributed greatly to the growth of bilateral relations
between China and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Rong said that the friendly cooperative ties have witnessed
continuous development in fields of politics, economy and culture
since the two countries forged diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
He added that China and the Philippines, both developing
nations, have experienced similar difficulties in history and face
the same task of building a strong and prosperous country and
upgrading their people's standard of living.
</P>
<P>
To support each other will help the common development of China
and the Philippines, Rong added.
</P>
<P>
Laurel, who is chairman for the Philippines National Centennial
Commission, said that he has been warmly welcomed during each of
his trips to China and has learned many new things here.
</P>
<P>
Laurel said he appreciated China's tremendous economic
development.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Laurel conveyed a letter from Fidel Ramos,
president of the Philippines to Chinese President Jiang Zemin, in
which Ramos invited the Chinese side to attend the Philippines
Centennial Exposition 1998. Rong thanked Laurel for the invitation.
</P>
<P>
Laurel and his party arrived here Sunday as guests of the
Chinese People's Institute of Foreign Affairs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
