<HEADLINE> China to Promote Share-holding System in State Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 15 (Xinhua) -- China had transformed more than
9,200 state enterprises to share-holding firms, by the end of
1996, with shares worth 600 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent working conference on reform of state
enterprises held here, China will continue to promote a
share-holding system in state enterprises in the next few years.
</P>
<P>
The share-holding system has been used as a major way to
revitalize Chinese state enterprises since 1993.
</P>
<P>
The symposium was sponsored by the State Commission for
Restructuring the Economy.  
