<HEADLINE> Zambia to Export More Electricity Power to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Plans are underway to export
Zambia's electric power to neighboring Tanzania, Namibia and
Botswana, Zambian Energy Minister Suresh Desai said.
</P>
<P>
Times of Zambia today quoted him as saying that an
environmental impact assessment has been carried out for the
proposed Zambia-Tanzania power interconnection.
</P>
<P>
The minister said his country would soon become the biggest
electricity exporter in the region if its power grinds are
connected to all member countries of the Southern Africa
Development Community (SADC) and its 6,000 megawatts potential is
exploited fully.
</P>
<P>
At the moment, Zambia has only developed 1,600 megawatts of
the power production potential, said the minister.
</P>
<P>
The whole project of connecting power grinds and developing
the power potential in the country is expected to cost more than
one billion U.S. Dollars. 
</P>
