<HEADLINE> Yunnan, Israel Cooperate on Flower Production, Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan and Israel plan to jointly
build China's largest flower production and exportation base in
this southwest province.
</P>
<P>
Planting and exporting flowers is the most attractive project
included in a bilateral economic cooperation package between
Yunnan and Israel, said Ora Namir, the Israeli ambassador to China.
</P>
<P>
Namir made the remark during a visit to Yunnan last week,
accompanied by a group of Israeli entrepreneurs. During her trip,
Yunnan and Israel decided to increase cooperation in agriculture
and other fields, and signed a series of cooperation agreements.
</P>
<P>
With a favorable climate, Yunnan is already China's top flower
producer with an annual output of more than 200 million bouquets
of fresh flowers. And flower planting plays a leading role in a
large biological resources development plan sponsored by the
provincial government.
</P>
<P>
However, Namir pointed out, Yunnan's flower industry is still
in its infancy, with a large quantity but few quality products,
and the flowers are mainly sold on the domestic market. Israel, as
the fourth biggest flower exporter in the world, can offer
advanced management expertise in developing the flower industry.
</P>
<P>
She said the two sides had shown great enthusiasm in
co-developing flower production in Yunnan, and signed, during her
current visit, cooperative projects on training, funding and
technological exchange.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said she has confidence in the broad prospects
for bilateral cooperation in flower production, and she hopes the
The Yunnan Flower Industrial Co. Ltd. -- the first Israeli
invested project -- will become an example for bilateral
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The company, with an investment of 1.5 million US dollars from
Israel, has completed the construction of six hectares of
high-standard greenhouses.
</P>
<P>
Namir added that Israel is ready to promote bilateral
cooperation in other fields such as science and technology,
medical appliances, telecommunications, and development of solar
energy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
