<HEADLINE> First Marche Restaurant Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Movenpick Marche, one of the
world's leading restaurant groups in Switzerland, and the Sincere
Company, one of Hong Kong's retail groups, today jointly opened a
restaurant in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Christian Karl Nothhaft, director of Movenpick Marche's
international operations, said the marketplace in Asia represents
an enormous potential for restaurant service.
</P>
<P>
He said that Movenpick Marche restaurants have enjoyed much
success throughout the world and he is looking forward to further
cooperation with sincere Company in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that his restaurant group will gain experiences in Hong
Kong so as to enter the Chinese mainland in the next few years.
</P>
<P>
The Marche restaurant concept was first launched in 1983 in
Stuttgart, Germany, by Movenpick Enterprises. After that, Marche
restaurants have been opened throughout Europe, North America,
other parts of Asia and the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
This year, there will be a total of 60 Marche restaurants with
over 2,300 employees in fourteen countries around the globe.
</P>
<P>
The Sincere Company operates six department stores in Hong
Kong. 
</P>
