<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Raise Water Price </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 15 (Xinhua) -- South African Water Affairs
and Forestry Minister Kader Asmal has warned that more water
price increase is on the way following the 12 percent increase in
water tariffs starting from April 1.
</P>
<P>
"The best way to make people cut their use of water is to put
up the cost, and the April increase was part of this process,"
local daily "The Citizen" today quoted Asmal as saying.
</P>
<P>
"South Africa is already experiencing water stress. The
equitable allocation of water and its efficient and beneficial
use will be critical for the sustainable economic and social
development of the country," he said.
</P>
<P>
South Africa is prone to recurring droughts and water
shortages. Although most major dams are full following recent
rains, this has not changed the long-term prognosis, local water
experts said.
</P>
<P>
"To ensure that the water in storage can bridge the droughts
to come, it is imperative to apply water conservation measures on
the continuous basis, of which a sound tariff policy is a key
element," Asmal stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
