<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afforestated Area Makes New Home for Swans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUHHOT, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Some 260 white swans recently
flied to a village in Wunniute Banner, an administrative division
in north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, for the fifth
time.
</P>
<P>
The village, in Erjiazi Township, was surrounded by desert some
twenty years ago. In 1986, the local government enhanced their
afforestation efforts when the second phase of the "three north
shelterbelt systems project" was started.
</P>
<P>
The forest coverage in the whole township has now reached 38
percent, and the environment has been significantly improved.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the fact that the swans will stay there for about
one month before continuing their trip to the north for the
summer, the township now has become home to over ten species of
wild animals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
