<HEADLINE> More Lawns, Better Living Environment For Shanghai's Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Pudong New Area is
making great efforts to beautify its environment through
afforestation in new construction area.
</P>
<P>
Lujiazui Development Company of Pudong New Area, Shanghai, has
taken a loan of 800 million yuan for building a park in the area's
Lujiazui Zone of Finance and Trade.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, the 100,000 sq m green land will
be covered by 65,000 sq m ever-green lawns grown with imported
strains dotted with lush green trees. An artificial lake covering
10,000 sq m and a fountain system will be sunk in the middle of
the area.
</P>
<P>
The park is to open to the public on July 1.
</P>
<P>
In building Pudong New Area, Shanghai has worked out
regulations that require planting of greenery surrounding
newly-built residential quarters, production factories, and
institutions. They also stipulate that large public facilities
must not be less than 30 percent of their respective total area of
land covered.
</P>
<P>
The municipal authorities have also set a goal of increasing
its forest cover to 35 percent in Pudong New Area by the early
21st century, with the per capita green land area amounting to 20
sq m.
</P>
<P>
Pudong has also set up a special team to help the enforcement
of the regulations.
</P>
<P>
During the past 17 years of forestation efforts, a total of 18
million ha of desolate area in China has been covered with green
plants, with the forest cover rate in the three areas rising from
five percent in 1977 to the current nine percent, according to
earlier reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
