<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Development Zones Play Bigger Role in Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Economic development zones
recorded a robust growth in east China's Fujian Province,
promoting an export-oriented economy.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has built three national development zones, two bonded
zones, five Taiwan-invested zones, two national tourist zones and
two high-tech development zones.
</P>
<P>
The zones generated an industrial output value of 43.1 billion
yuan last year, accounting for 23.5 percent of the total
industrial output value yielded by enterprises at or above the
township level.
</P>
<P>
Their export value totalled 2.73 billion US dollars last year,
making up a quarter of the province's total.
</P>
<P>
These development zones have drawn an overseas investment of
4.9 billion US dollars in building 2,256 projects. Some 1,500
firms have started operation so far.
</P>
<P>
These zones have given priority to the development of light
industry, electronic, textile, and food industry. Some hi-tech
companies in Fuxing Rongqiao Development Zone and Fuzhou
Development Zone are in the forefront of the country in production
scale and in the percentage of science and technology played in
production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
