<HEADLINE> Scholars Sought to Lend Hands in Environment Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Vice-governor Liu Shuying of
northeast China's Jilin province recently visited China's
prestigious Qinghua University to seek cooperation on
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The vice-governor invited scholars in Qinghua University to
give advice on how to maintain sustained development in Jilin's
Changbaishan mountain areas, and how to protect the wetlands and
cranes, rare living spieces, in the west part of the province.
</P>
<P>
During past years a number of scholars from Qinghua University
have made on-the-spot investigations in Jilin, especially in the
Changbaishan mountain areas and the west wetlands areas.
</P>
<P>
According to Fang Huijian, director of Qinghua University's
21st Century Development School, an expert group led by him will
go to Jilin this June for further investigations and research.
</P>
</TEXT>
