<HEADLINE> Road Mishap Kills 9 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed and 13
others injured when an overpacked jeep in which they were
traveling dashed against a stationary truck in India's Madhya
Pradesh on Monday, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to police, the accident occurred when the driver of
the jeep lost control of the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
The injured, five of them seriously, have been rushed to
hospital. 
</P>
