<HEADLINE> Hungary Maintains Good Economic Growth: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Hungary will become the "only"
country in Eastern Europe which maintains stable and sustained
economic growth, Hungarian Prime Minister Horn Gyula told a news
conference today.
</P>
<P>
Horn said, his country saw hopeful prospect in the economy, and
the economic growth had surpassed that in the government's
administrative program made in 1994. It was not necessary for
the government to shrink the residents' consumption now, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said Hungary would develop an advanced footing in reforms of
health services, education and administration.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister expected 60 percent residents would be the
beneficiaries of the market economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
