<HEADLINE> Swedish Volvo to Expand Production in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Swedish automaker Volvo is
to expand its production in India by building a truck factory
outside the southern city of Bangalore.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed recently by Indian Industrial
Minister R.V. Deshpandi and the Volvo company, the factory is to
start operation next summer with a yearly capacity of some 4,000
units using parts from Sweden. 
