<HEADLINE> Visitor Arrivals to Macao Drop Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The number of visitors from Taiwan, China's mainland, Britain,
Thailand, the United States, the Republic of Korea and Japan,
however, rose in a row.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the number of Taiwanese visitors rose by the
largest margin of 61.4 percent, comparing with the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan and Macao have had direct air links since the Macao
International Airport went into operation in November 1995. Many
Taiwanese businessmen choose to fly to the mainland on the
quasi-direct flight via Macao.
</P>
<P>
The figures show that in February, 705,425 visitor arrivals
were recorded, down 2.0 percent from the same month of last year.
</P>
<P>
More than 8.15 million visitors arrived in Macao last year,
and the government expects this year's figure will reach nine
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
