<HEADLINE> Officials Examine Free Trade of the Americas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Officials from 34 American
countries today began a four-day meeting in Rio de Janeiro to
reach a consensus leading to a Free Trade Agreement for the
Americas (FTAA).
</P>
<P>
Nine Latin American nations, four from the Southern Common
Market and five from the Andean Pact, have a common position in
stressing the need for a gradual process of liberalization after
the year 2005. The United States wants an earlier date.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be followed by a forum of trade ministers of
the American continent from May 12 to 17 in the Brazilian state of
Minas Gerais. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
