<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada to Co-host Knowledge Conference with World Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian government said today
that it is co-hosting with the World Bank an international
conference on harnessing knowledge and information for
international development.
</P>
<P>
The conference will be held in Toronto from June 22 to 25.
</P>
<P>
The conference, entitled Global Knowledge 97 -- Knowledge for
Development in the Information Age, will bring together some 1,200
delegates of government, industry, multinational and
non-government organizations from more than 100 countries.
</P>
<P>
Participants will explore how information technology and
transfer of knowledge can contribute to global poverty reduction
and sustainable progress.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to focus on three major themes: understanding
the role of information in development; sharing ways and means of
harnessing knowledge for development; and building new
partnerships to empower the poor, foster dialogue and strengthen
the information/knowledge resources of developing countries.
</P>
<P>
They will also examine areas such as policy and regulatory
frameworks, science and technology, life-long learning, distance
education and governance.
</P>
<P>
United Nations Secretary General Kofi Annan is among the
international leaders invited to the conference, the Canadian
government said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
