<HEADLINE> Canadian Man Kills Wife, Four Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- A Canadian man shot his wife and
four children Sunday before setting fire to their home and
ending his life with the gun, reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The six family members were found dead inside their burning
farmhouse Sunday afternoon at Orangeville, some 50 kilometers
northwest of Toronto.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the couple, aged 37 and 36, had been separated
for over a month and the woman had planned to finalize divorce and
pick up their children, two sons and two daughters between the
ages of 15 and 11.
</P>
<P>
The mother had made arrangements with a local shelter that if
she was not back by three p.m. then they would contact the police.
</P>
<P>
When the police rushed to the scene just after 4 p.m., the house
had already been engulfed in flames. 
</P>
</TEXT>
