<HEADLINE> Swedish King: More Cooperation with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Swedish enterprises, especially
the medium and small-sized ones, should start cooperation with
their Chinese counterparts as soon as possible, King Carl XVI
Gustaf said to visiting Chinese Vice Premier Wu Bangguo today.
</P>
<P>
Recalling his visit to China, the king said that he was deeply
impressed by the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
He said Sweden attaches great importance to foreign trade,
particularly trade with China and he hoped that Swedish
enterprises could get a better knowledge about the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
Wu, who had already toured the renowned mobile phone company
Ericsson, the automaker Volvo and ABB electric company, said their
advanced technologies and management must be conducive to
cooperation with their Chinese counterparts.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China, enjoying a stable political situation
and sustained economic growth, is willing to further cooperation
with Sweden, especially in trade and economy.
</P>
<P>
Swedish Industry and Commerce Minister Anders Sundstrom also
held talks with Wu today to exchange views on specific joint
projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
