<HEADLINE> Chilean President Back Home After Visit to France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Eduardo Frei
was back after a five-day visit to France.
</P>
<P>
Frei said at the Santiago International Airport that during his
visit the two countries signed eight agreements of cooperation on
education and health as well as on combating drug trafficking and
money laundering.
</P>
<P>
He said he met with his French counterpart Jacques Chirac,
Prime Minister Alain Juppe, Education Minister Francois Bayrou and
other senior French officials.
</P>
<P>
He also inaugurated an exhibition on the late singer Violeta
Parra in the Louvre Museum, a Chilean art show and honored
Roberto Matta, a painter, with the Gabriel Mistral award. 
</P>
