<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Adopts New Housing Loan Scheme </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
adopted a new housing loan scheme recently to assist low income
group families, according to official sources today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the scheme is open to all persons
receiving a monthly income below 100 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
They stated that already 6.14 million U.S. dollars were
earmarked for the loan scheme under a US aid scheme.
</P>
<P>
The loan of upto 2,190 US dollars will be offered to persons
below the age of 60 who could set apart 35 percent of their income
for the repayment of loans.
</P>
<P>
Interest will be at 17 percent and the loan is repayable in 15
years, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be provided for building or purchasing a house,
buying land for building a house and extension to an existing
house, the sources added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
