April 30 and May 1 in Tokyo concerning a new fishery treaty
covering operations in waters within both sides' economic zones.
</P>
<P>
Ikeda said he hoped to conclude a new pact by summer, but Yoo
argued that the two countries have to wait and see how talks for a
similar fishery pact turn out between Japan and China, the
officials said. 
