<HEADLINE> Gale Kills Five in Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Five Ukrainian fishermen died in the
Sea of Azov Monday when their boat capsized in high seas whipped
up by a gale.
</P>
<P>
More than 490 houses were flooded and 1282 people were forced
to flee their homes.
</P>
<P>
The strong winds also brought heavy rain to the Donetsk and
Zaporozje Oblasts regions along the Azov Sea.
</P>
<P>
The government had only evacuated 186 of the people forced to
flee their homes, officials said.
</P>
<P>
They were estimating losses caused by the disaster and said the
strong gusts and heavy rain were a deadly blow to the sluggish
agriculture of the two areas.
</P>
<P>
A week ago, a snow storm attacked the west of the country while
downpours hit the southern part. One person was killed when his
house collapsed in the Crimean Republic. 
