<HEADLINE> Thailand Proposes Economic Circle of Mekong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Thailand has proposed an economic
circle among Mekong river basin countries and will discuss the
idea next week through a round of "golf diplomacy."
</P>
<P>
Thai Foreign Minister Prachuab Chaiyasarn has invited his
counterparts of Cambodia, Laos, Vietnam and Myanmar to play golf
in Bangkok and Pattaya on April 20-21 and to discuss the economic
cooperation idea.
</P>
<P>
The economic circle will initially involve northeast Thailand
with southern Laos and northwest Cambodia, with the possible
extension to central Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Arid northeast Thailand is the least developed region in the
country.
</P>
<P>
During the golfing sessions, the Thai foreign minister will
also ask his counterparts of Cambodia, Laos and Myanmar about the
internal situation of their respective countries.
</P>
<P>
Last year the association of southeast Asian nations (ASEAN)
decided to admit the three countries into the grouping together.
</P>
<P>
However, recent violence in Myanmar and Cambodia may jeopardize
the possibility.  
</P>
