<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest Chinese Region Making Headway In WFP Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 15 (Xinhua) -- A World Food Program (WFP)
project is doing well in northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region and serves as a model in promoting local agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The project, providing relief with free grain, named "4071",
covers three poor counties in the region, with a planned
investment of 110.47 million yuan-worth of grains. It involves 10
sub-projects in water conservancy, farmland improvement, and
science and technology training.
</P>
<P>
A total of 43.15 million yuan has been put in the project,
which started in 1994. The project areas produced 54 million kg of
grains last year, and had 347 kg per capita, 10 percent higher
than areas that the projects do not cover.
</P>
<P>
The region has set up a special office to supervise the
operation of the project. Nearly 2,000 projects of varying sizes
have been built to ensure water for irrigation, consumption by man
and livestock.
</P>
<P>
Eight thousand ha of hillside fields have been terraced into
farmland, and 3,000 ha planted with trees. Local farmers collected
7.87 million yuan by planting grass and breeding livestock, over
the past three years.
</P>
<P>
Agro-sciences like plastic sheeting technique were introduced
into the project areas and are contributing greatly to local
agricultural development. More and more villagers are
participating in training classes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
