<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- China's first national
experimental zone geared to new and high-tech development in the
field of agriculture opened recently in northwest China's Shaanxi
Province, "China Information" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Built with approval of the State Council, the zone covers 20 sq
km at Yangling in central Shaanxi. More than 4,100 agro-scientists
specializing in 64 subjects are working in the zone.
</P>
