<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Proposes Strategic Partnership With Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine proposed a strategic
partnership with Israel, Gennady Udovenko, Ukrainian Foreign
Minister, said here today, because there is no political problem
between them.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko made the remarks after meeting with visiting Israeli
Trade and Industry Minister Natan Sharansky. He said Ukraine is
also willing to be a mediator between Israel and the Arabian world
over the Middle East issue.
</P>
<P>
He added that Ukraine is interested in cooperating with Israel
in ship-building, space industry, plane industry, sea
transportation and trade.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume between Ukraine and Israel reached 100 million U.S
dollars in 1996, five times the figure of 1990. There are now 80
Ukrainian-Israeli joint ventures in Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
He said the two sides also discussed issues concerning the
interests of the Jewish people living in Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
About 350,000 Ukrainian Jewish have immigrated to Israel in the
past decade, and have become a supporting force for a better
Ukrainian-Israeli relations.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma also stressed the
political strategic ties and economic cooperations between the two
countries when meeting with the visiting Israeli minister.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
