<HEADLINE> Guatemala Soccer Stadium to Reopen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 14 (Xinhua) -- World soccer ruling body FIFA
has authorised the re-opening of Guatemala City's Mateo Flores
Stadium, where 82 people were killed in a tragedy on October 16
because of overcrowding, reports reaching here said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
To comply with FIFA recommendations, stadium authorities
developed a new system to prevent counterfeit tickets, added
emergency exits and built new retaining walls, among other
measures, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Overcrowding at one entrance of the stadium during a World Cup
qualifying match between Guatemala and Costa Rica sent a crushing
wave of fans cascading down the stands toward the field.
</P>
<P>
The IV Cup of Nations, a tournament of Central American soccer
teams, will be held at the stadium on Wednesday and
Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
