<HEADLINE> Multinational Force to Land in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 14 (Xinhua) -- A 1,000-strong multinational force
will land at the Albanian port of Durres after midnight tonight to
protect humanitarian aid supplies to this Balkan country, Italian
Chief of Defense Staff Admiral Guido Venturoni said today.
</P>
<P>
The Italian-led force comprising Italian, French and Spanish
troops will carry out a mission code-named "Operation Alba,"
Venturoni told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
But he did not reveal the precise time for the start of the
landing.
</P>
<P>
The operation will allow food supplies to be sent in and safely
stockpiled in the country and make a limited distribution possible.
</P>
<P>
In the meanwhile, Venturoni said, a group of 150 Italian
soldiers will fly to Tirana airport to join the advance party
which was deployed Friday.
</P>
<P>
The first 10 days of the operation will focus on securing
bridgeheads at Durres, Tirana airport and Vlore, the admiral said.
</P>
<P>
The force will build up to its maximum of some 6,000 troops in
three months when contingents from Turkey, Greece, Denmark,
Romania and Austria come to join it, he said.
</P>
<P>
The commander of the force is Italian general Luciano Forlani
and the headquarters for the force will be set up in Tirana,
capital of Albania.
</P>
<P>
In Athens, Greek military sources said that the first units of
the 760-strong Greek contingent are expected to travel to Vlore by
sea Thursday to be followed by the rest to fly to Tirana Saturday
and next Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
