<DOCNO> XIE19970415.0256 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NZ Tries to Repair Ties with Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 15 (Xinhua) -- It is still not clear today
whether Iran will go ahead with its ban on trade with New Zealand
after the meeting between the NZ Foreign Minister and the Iranian
Ambassador here last night.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Don McKinnon held emergency talks with Iranian
Ambassador Mehdi Sazegara last night in an effort to avert a
diplomatic rift which threatens trade between the two countries.
McKinnon said this morning he hopes the trade crisis with Iran
could be solved this week.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian government has ordered the suspension of all trade
agreements with NZ because of NZ's support for a German court
ruling that top Iranian officials had been involved in the murder
of four dissidents in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
NZ has recalled its Ambassador from Tehran and Sazegara had
been withdrawn by his government and was to leave NZ today.
</P>
<P>
But last night, Sazegara said he might not leave after all and
was seeking advice from his government. He also said that he had
not received any formal advice from Iran of a trade ban.
</P>
<P>
NZ exports to Iran amount to 170 million dollars (120 million
US dollars) last year, mainly meat, butter, wool and fish. NZ
exporters said that they are not worried about Iran's trade ban
because the amounts exported to the country are not very big.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970415.0257 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qingdao to Further Open up Port of Entry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, April 13 (Xinhua) -- East China's coastal city of
Qingdao will further open up its port of entry and strengthen its
management in line with international norms this year.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao aims to build a grand port of entry combining land, sea
and air facilities in 1997, according to its annual conference on
port of entry.
</P>
<P>
The port will speed up the reform of its inspection system to
facilitate customs procedures and border inspection, as well as
medical check-up and quaraintine of animal and plant, thus
creating a good environment for the city's economic development
and further opening up.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao will open one or two air routes to Singapore this year,
and make market surveys on more passenger and cargo air transport
services between Qingdao and southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
It will also prepare for the initiation of more shipping lines
between Qingdao and the Republic of Korea and Japan in addition to
its efforts of opening up railway port for greater economic
expansion of the city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
