<HEADLINE> National Reconciliation Key to Afghanistan Issue: China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Ambassador Wang Xuexian,
Chinese deputy permanent representative to the United Nations,
said today that national reconciliation is the key to the
Afghanistan question.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Wang noted that the final settlement of the question
depends on the Afghan people themselves. The parties concerned
should show a sincere political will to settle their differences
through peaceful negotiations, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Wang made the remarks at an open debate on the
situation of Afghanistan and the ways to promote a negotiated
settlement of the conflict.
</P>
<P>
He said that the parties concerned should immediately implement
a cease-fire and cease hostilities. "In our view, the attempt to
use military means to settle the conflict only lead to aggravation
of the conflict, plunging the Afghan people into misery
indefinitely."
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Wang also expressed support for the good offices
provided by Secretary-General Kofi Annan and his special envoy and
hoped that the United Nations would continue to play a leading
role in this field.
</P>
<P>
More than a dozen countries are scheduled to address the
Security Council on the subject. 
