<HEADLINE> US to Decide Food Aid to DPRK in 24 Hours </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States will make an
announcement within 24 hours on whether it would provide new food
aid to the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), the State
Department said today.
</P>
<P>
"The United States is now finishing its internal deliberations
on the issue of whether or not to respond to the augmented appeal
of the World Food Program for a greater level of food assistance
to North Korea, and I would expect within the next 24 hours that I
will have an announcement to make on that issue," State Department
spokesman Nicholas Burns said.
</P>
<P>
Burns also revealed that the United States and the DPRK had
agreed to hold talks in New York on May 12-13 on bilateral issues.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, DPRK officials will give response to a U.S.-South
Korean proposal on four-party peace talks at a meeting in New York
with U.S. and South Korean officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
